can do a cylinder to stock dimensions based on provided make model and year if you would like us to provide a new aftermarket piston simply choose the type you would like and indicate it on our service order form and send it in with your cylinder keep in mind that ordering a piston through millennium on your service order form does entitle you to a  discount off the retail price of the piston as well as any other aftermarket parts like gaskets or bearings that you may need so save some money and order through us qdo i need to take my cylinder apart a click to reveal you can send in just your cylinder all components you want serviced or even your entire engine for us to provide engine rebuilding services for you we recommend calling one of our service technicians to discuss all options available for your specific needs millennium technologies will not be held liable for any damaged or broken parts that may result from disassembly this includes cylinder head bolts please remove them from the cylinder we will not be liable for any damaged or broken head bolts if removing a head bolt results in the need for a helicoil the customer will be contacted to be notified of the additional costs qwhen sending in a cylinder do the power valves need to be removed or is that part of the cylinder service a click to reveal no we recommend that you send the entire power valve assembly along with your cylinder and take advantage of our power valve service qdo you buy used or core cylinders a click to reveal yes we often will purchase your used cylinders without requiring any purchase or exchange with us but it depends on your specific cylinder and the condition it is in feel free to call us to discuss selling us your used cylinders qdo you sell cylinders outright a click to reveal we do sell cylinders outright depending on inventory levels and availability qdo you have a core cylinder for my application a click to reveal we carry over  cylinders in our core inventory to fit almost any application we recommend calling one of our sales technicians to discuss all options available for your specific core needs qhow long does it take to get my cylinder back a click to reveal typical turn around times are  business days for single cylinder and head services  business days for mono blocks inlines and integral top cases  business days on automotive and engine building services qwhat are my options for repair on my order can i get by doing it cheaper a click to reveal there are always many repair or modifications options for your cylinder please call one of our sales technicians to discuss what range of options and pricing are available for your needs qhow big can i go a click to reveal overbore or oversizing options vary by model and application we recommend calling one of our sales technicians to discuss all options available for your specific needs qi am doing a big bore do i need to send any parts besides my cylinder a click to reveal when doing may big bore kits it is necessary to modify other parts of the motor often times the power valve assembly andor cylinder head require changes to accept your new bore size failure to modify these parts will result in power loss andor engine failure if you are unsure of your needs please contact us qi am doing my own overboring what size do i bore to a click to reveal your cylinder should be bored to ” ±” over your finish bore size in other words take your piston size add clearance and then add ” when doing your final pass it is a good idea to use a new bit to ensure we receive a smooth groove free surface that is ready for plating if left undersized or too rough we will need to rebore your cylinder negating your attempt to save cost and time please do not hone your cylinders at this point honing on bare aluminum forces oil into the casting and can result in excessive porosity qwhat is porosity and will it affect my engine a click to reveal porosity is gas trapped in the base metal aluminum during casting these “holes” are exposed when the cylinder is machined or subjected to various chemicals in the plating process the pits are usually small in size and in good castings few and far between when kept under acceptable levels porosity will not adversely affect the performance or longevity of the engine in fact it will improve lubrication the pits will not cause the coating to peel nor will a ring hook on them as far as our specifications on porosity our cylinders carry a lifetime warranty against defects in materials and workmanship therefore through extensive testing we have found that porosity is a cosmetic problem only in our pursuit to have both cosmetic and functional perfection we do everything possible to remove these pits in some cases this is not possible so we release the cylinder only in cases where it will not affect performance qwhat does oleofilic mean a click to reveal oleofilic is a natural tendency to absorb oil coatings that are oleofilic help the oil retention of the coating and reduces the wear on the surface qwhen i do a big bore what should i jet my carburetor to a click to reveal please see our jetting guidelines qwhat are the advantages to running a plated cylinder compared to a cast cylinder a click to reveal in most cases your cylinder was not designed to run with an iron liner installing a sleeve not only adds weight to your cylinder increases operating temperatures but you will also be sacrificing the unbeatable wear characteristics of an nsc coating an iron liner will wear  times faster than a plated cylinder resulting in too much piston to wall clearance which can result in engine failures in addition replating your cylinder with nsc will almost always be less expensive and less time consuming qcan you plate cast iron a click to reveal we can plate many materials cast iron included by plating cast iron the cylinder will have all the benefits of nsc except the heat transfer these benefits include  times better wear resistance more horsepower and better ring seal qdo you offer porting packages for my two stroke and four stroke application a click to reveal we offer many porting options for two and four stroke applications we recommend calling one of our sales technicians to discuss all options available for your specific needs qwhat do the packages that you offer give me as far as horsepower gain a click to reveal depending on what your performance needs are we can offer power gains and performance improvement for just about any application we recommend calling one of our sales technicians to discuss all options available for your specific needs qis there damage that can’t be fixed – what then a click to reveal most times we can fix just about anything however there are few scenarios that the damage just can’t be repaired we recommend calling one of our sales technicians to discuss all options available for your specific needs if repair can’t be completed qwhat is the difference between what you and your competition do a click to reveal we are the largest replating facility in the world we use those resources to ensure that we have the highest quality and environmental standards in the industry with that volume there isn’t anything new to us we produce cylinders for governments original manufactures race teams and development engineers as well as thousands of customers just like you dealer status qdo you have dealer discounts a click to reveal we do have dealer programs for customers who are in the industry and providing service and repairs on powersports equipment for the general public qwhat do i get for becoming a dealer a click to reveal by becoming a dealer you get additional discounts on all services provided as well as discounts on all oem and aftermarket parts purchased from millennium technologies qdoes becoming a dealer have a buy in or other costs a click to reveal there is no cost to this process we only need a copy of your state tax id business license or resale certificate a website and or business listing showing you are in the powersports repair and service business shipping qdo you receive international orders and how much will it cost a click to reveal we will gladly accept international orders we can return ship through the u s postal service ups or fedex since it is hard for us to get exact shipping estimates we have provided you the links to these couriers shipping cost estimate websites there you should be able to get at least a rough estimate on the shipping costs to and from our facility if you are within the united states these tools are also excellent for calculating ground and air shipment costs ups fedex customers please be aware that any shipping insurance or duty and daxes are also not included in the cost estimate qis shipping included a click to reveal no shipping is not figured into the posted pricing please call one of our sales technicians and we can get a shipping quote for you or you can use one of these sights to gain that information ups or fedex qhow can i get my cylinder serviced and back to me the next day a click to reveal we can ship cylinders from our core inventory out same day utilizing our cylinder exchange program but if you want your cylinder repaired normal turn around times will apply qdo you offer a rush service a click to reveal we offer rush services to get cylinders through our process in half the normal turn time parts  engine building qdo you fix — cam journals multi cylinder crankshafts a click to reveal we do not perform these repairs in house but we can have them provided for you qcan i get oem parts from you or do i need to get them from a dealer a click to reveal we would be happy to source all your oem parts needs price and delivery time will be quoted before payment qdo you set ring end gap a click to reveal no we do not ring end gap should be measured and set at the time of engine assembly by you or your engine builder qcan i drop my bike off and just have you fix it a click to reveal you can ship cylinders your entire engine or drop off your entire bike here at millennium and we can have needed repairs made or services provided we recommend calling one of our sales technicians to discuss all options available for your specific needs qwill this be covered under warranty a click to reveal our plating services are covered by a limited lifetime warranty there is no warranty offered by millennium technologies on repairs or parts not manufactured by millennium technologies heads qdo you sell heads a click to reveal we do sell complete heads outright depending on inventory levels and availability qfour stroke head repair do you guys set the cam and lash and will the head be ready to just bolt on when i receive a click to reveal no we cannot set valve clearances if we only have the head and not the complete engine this is due to the fact that clearances will not be accurate until the head is properly torqued onto the engine block with the head gasket in place payment  pricing qhow and when do i pay for my order a click to reveal we recommend having a form of payment on file to be charged upon completion of work performed or at time of order to ensure no additional delays in getting your cylinders and parts shipped back to you qhow do i pay for my repair a click to reveal we recommend having a form of payment on file to be charged upon completion of work performed or at time of order as to ensure no additional delays in getting your cylinders and parts shipped back to you qif i can find a cheaper price on my parts will you match the price i find a click to reveal in most situations we can provide cheaper pricing on parts purchased from most retailers however we do not match pricing listed on online sources such as e bay or amazon q can  how do i get a bigger discount a click to reveal we have kit and service option packages that can qualify for additional discounts we recommend calling one of our sales technicians to discuss all options available for your specific needs sponsorships qdo you sponsor riders and if so what are the requirements a click to reveal yes we are always interested in interesting marketing opportunities if you have an interesting project race program or unique way to promote our products services and brands please send your marketing proposal to sponsorshipmillenniumtechnet and we will be happy to investigate a mutually beneficial partnership revolution performance qdo i need to fill out a work order a click to reveal yes all work must include a work order form or send in an estimate complete the form online print it and include with your parts we ask that you fill these forms out before sending in your part so that we have all instructions and contact info ready if you prefer you can print out a hard copy of the forms and complete them by hand feel free to call us at  or email us before or after business hours at inforevolutionperformancenet and we can provide you with an estimate that you can print out and ship in the box with your items qwhat guidelines do you use to bore cases a click to reveal revolution performance bores cases according to cylinder manufacturer’s tolerances we have a detailed process for each manufacturer and may choose to position center case bolt as a through bolt versus a tapped blind hole for added structural integrity the positioning of this bolt is critical and must align with case opening so it does not damage cylinders upon installation weeping at center case bolt may occur if not sealed properly qwhat specifications does revolution follow a click to reveal all specifications for our work meet or exceed oem specifications qwhat guidelines do you use to install crankshafts a click to reveal our crankshafts will install as any stock flywheel per the manufacturer’s recommendations we hold strict tolerances according to or exceeding manufacturer’s recommendations qwhere do you measure crankshaft total indicated runout a click to reveal we measure total indicated runout by going off the tip of the pinion shaft qcan i speak directly with a technician a click to reveal yes you may contact a technician to answer any question regarding our work or process between  am   pm cst monday through friday you can also send us an email during or after business hours at inforevolutionperformancenet qi have a question on the assembly procedures what do i do a click to reveal refer to the factory service manual for information on assembly procedures or feel free to call us between  am   pm cst monday through friday or contact us by email during or after business hours at inforevolutionperformancenet qhow long will you store a crankshaft without a work order a click to reveal crankshafts sent to revolution performance without a work order or direction of service will be considered abandoned after  months and become property of revolution performance qwhat is the timken endplay set at a click to reveal we install races and set timken bearing endplay between ”  ” qhow do i get a dealer discount a click to reveal to receive a dealer discount a dealer application must be approved and on file upon completion of work qi work out of my garage part time can i be a revolution performance dealer a click to reveal no we require all dealers to be fulltime dealers who work on vtwin motorcycles harley davidson victory and indian motorcycles as their fulltime job we understand there are many great mechanics who work on the side however we must protect our dealers and their fulltime job qwhat dealers do you recommend a click to reveal we work with many great dealers all over the world please see our dealer locator map to see which dealers fit your needs and location feel free to give us a call at  and we can provide you with a dealer recommendation based on your specific needs that you have at that moment qhow are packages shipped a click to reveal all packages are shipped ups regular ground unless requested and stated        copyright   millennium technologies llc all rights res